<paragraph id="8BFF5047FFE7AC20C000F9D30699917E" blockId="6.[811,1457,1197,1835]" pageId="6" pageNumber="181">
SEED MORPHOLOGY. — The seeds of 
<taxonomicName id="4C402BC4FFE7AC20C7AAF9D300A1910E" authority="Z.Rostami, Assadi &amp; F.Ghahrem." authorityName="Z. Rostami, Assadi &amp; F. Ghahrem." authorityYear="2019" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Caryophyllaceae" genus="Bufonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="6" pageNumber="181" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="iranica" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B9348C55FFE7AC20C7AAF9D307E292E4" box="[1159,1249,1505,1528]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="181">B. iranica</emphasis>
Z.Rostami, Assadi &amp; F.Ghahrem.
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A207312EFFE7AC20C081F9C900FB910E" box="[940,1016,1531,1554]" pageId="6" pageNumber="181" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
are brown, orbicular with lateral hilum, and about 
<quantity id="4CB8FDA2FFE7AC20C041FA2700A49130" box="[876,935,1557,1581]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="6" pageNumber="181" unit="mm" value="2.0">2 mm</quantity>
diameter. The surface has elongated testa cells on the wing and hilum of the seed (
<figureCitation id="137B4CC2FFE7AC20C76DFA1D077B915B" box="[1088,1144,1583,1607]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="5.[132,143,1618,1636]" captionTargetBox="[133,1455,215,1586]" captionTargetId="figure-161@5.[698,1267,762,1312]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIG. 2. — A-E, Details of morphological characters of Bufonia iranica Z.Rostami,Assadi &amp; F.Ghahrem.,sp. nov.(Mozaffarian 70066): A, calyx;B, upper part of sepal; C, mature ovary; D, mature open ovary; E, petal; F, G, Bufonia enervis Boiss. (Iranshahr &amp; Termeh 12159-E): F, calyx; G, petal; H-M, B. iranica Z.Rostami, Assadi &amp; F.Ghahrem, sp. nov.: H, seed; I, close view of the seed surface from median part of the seed at the position between hilum and abfunicular side; J, K, close views of the seed surface at the abfunicular side; L, close view of the seed surface from median part of the seed at the hilum; M, close view of anticlinal border between testa cells. Scale bars: A, D, E, 1.2 mm; B, 0.38 mm; C, 0.97 mm; F, 0.87 mm; G, 0. 82 mm; H, 1 mm; I-L, 100 µm; M, 10 µm." pageId="6" pageNumber="181">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
H-M). The periclinal wall of the testa cells is slightly convex. The anticlinal walls are Zip-shaped.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C35A03CCFFE7AC20C000FA4800F69036" pageId="6" pageNumber="181" type="distribution">
