</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C35A03CCFFE7AC21C000FB6000059332" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="182" pageId="6" pageNumber="181" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BFF5047FFE7AC20C000FB6000BE9076" blockId="6.[811,1455,1874,2028]" box="[813,957,1874,1900]" pageId="6" pageNumber="181">DESCRIPTION</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFF5047FFE7AC21C000FB4300059332" blockId="6.[811,1455,1874,2028]" lastBlockId="7.[131,775,534,1070]" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="182" pageId="6" pageNumber="181">
Perennial, woody at base. Stems numerous, 
<quantity id="4CB8FDA2FFE7AC20C62AFB4306739090" box="[1287,1392,1905,1932]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.85" metricValueMax="2.5" metricValueMin="1.2" pageId="6" pageNumber="181" unit="cm" value="18.5" valueMax="25.0" valueMin="12.0">12-25 cm</quantity>
high, erect, rigid, glabrous puberulent, simple or with short branches parallel to the stem; internodes 
<quantity id="4CB8FDA2FFE7AC20C7D5FB83066C90D0" box="[1272,1391,1969,1996]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.75" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="3.5" pageId="6" pageNumber="181" unit="mm" value="37.5" valueMax="40.0" valueMin="35.0">35-40 mm</quantity>
long. Basal leaves connate and sheathing, lower leaves 
<quantity id="4CB8FDA2FFE7AC20C66AFBE306AC90F0" box="[1351,1455,2001,2028]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.0" metricValueMax="10.0" metricValueMin="8.0" pageId="6" pageNumber="181" unit="mm" value="9.0" valueMax="10.0" valueMin="8.0">8-10 mm</quantity>
long, upper leaves shorter, subulate, rigid, adhesive to stem, ciliolate on the margin. Bracts 
<quantity id="4CB8FDA2FFE6AC21C2CDFE040120954D" box="[480,547,566,593]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="182" unit="mm" value="3.0">3 mm</quantity>
long, ovate-oblong, acute, ciliolate on the margin. Inflorescence compact. Flowers crowded in few flowered (2-5 flowers) terminal or lateral cymes, subsessile or very shortly pedicellate. Pedicels very short, rigid, glabrous. The outer pair sepals 
<quantity id="4CB8FDA2FFE6AC21C140FE8701C495CC" box="[621,711,693,720]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="182" unit="mm" value="4.5" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="4.0">4-5 mm</quantity>
long, broadly ovate, acute, 5-nerved, with white 
<quantity id="4CB8FDA2FFE6AC21C160FEE701CC95EC" box="[589,719,725,752]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" metricValueMax="7.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="182" unit="mm" value="0.6" valueMax="0.7" valueMin="0.5">0.5-0.7 mm</quantity>
wide scarious margin, straw yellow or black red. The inner pair sepals 
<quantity id="4CB8FDA2FFE6AC21C3E7FF270222942C" box="[202,289,789,816]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="182" unit="mm" value="5.5" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="5.0">5-6 mm</quantity>
long, broadly ovate, acute, 5-nerved, middle nerve excurrent, with 
<quantity id="4CB8FDA2FFE6AC21C255FF0702B9944C" box="[376,442,821,848]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="182" unit="mm" value="1.0">1 mm</quantity>
broad white scarious margin, straw color, pale purple or pallid purpurine or reddish, glabrous. Petals 
<quantity id="4CB8FDA2FFE6AC21C23EFF4702839493" box="[275,384,885,912]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.25" metricValueMax="5.5" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="182" unit="mm" value="5.25" valueMax="5.5" valueMin="5.0">5-5.5 mm</quantity>
long, broadly ovate, acute. Stamens 8, 
<quantity id="4CB8FDA2FFE6AC21C3B3FFA703F794B3" box="[158,244,917,944]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" pageId="7" pageNumber="182" unit="mm" value="3.5">3.5 mm</quantity>
long. Ovary with 4 ovules. Capsule compressed, 
<quantity id="4CB8FDA2FFE6AC21C3AEFF8603DF94D3" box="[131,220,948,975]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" pageId="7" pageNumber="182" unit="mm" value="3.5">3.5 mm</quantity>
long, semi-elliptic. Seeds brown, 2 × 
<quantity id="4CB8FDA2FFE6AC21C1BCFF8701DA94D3" box="[657,729,949,975]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="182" unit="mm" value="2.0">2 mm</quantity>
, orbicular, laterally compressed, with few tubercles. In terms of exomorphology, the surface of the seed is constructed of regularly arranged elongate cells with zip-shaped margins.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
