<subSubSection id="C35A03CCFFE6AC21C3A9F867000492B2" pageId="7" pageNumber="182" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BFF5047FFE6AC21C3A9F86703EF9371" blockId="7.[131,777,1109,1454]" box="[132,236,1109,1135]" pageId="7" pageNumber="182">REMARKS</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFF5047FFE6AC21C3A9F846000492B2" blockId="7.[131,777,1109,1454]" pageId="7" pageNumber="182">
The new species is close to 
<taxonomicName id="4C402BC4FFE6AC21C28FF84601479392" box="[418,580,1140,1166]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Caryophyllaceae" genus="Bufonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="7" pageNumber="182" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="enervis">
<emphasis id="B9348C55FFE6AC21C28FF84601479392" box="[418,580,1140,1166]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="182">Bufonia enervis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but it differs with having glabrous pedicels; longer sepals (4-6 not 
<quantity id="4CB8FDA2FFE6AC21C187F8A6000693B2" box="[682,773,1172,1198]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="182" unit="mm" value="3.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="3.0">3-4 mm</quantity>
long), and wider sepals (&gt;0.5 not 
<quantity id="4CB8FDA2FFE6AC21C127F886016793D2" box="[522,612,1204,1231]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="182" unit="mm" value="0.5">0.5 mm</quantity>
wide) broadly ovate in shape (not ovate-lanceolate); longer petals (5-5.5 not 
<quantity id="4CB8FDA2FFE6AC21C382F8C102329212" box="[175,305,1267,1294]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" metricValueMax="3.5" metricValueMin="2.5" pageId="7" pageNumber="182" unit="mm" value="3.0" valueMax="3.5" valueMin="2.5">2.5-3.5 mm</quantity>
long), broadly ovate in shape (not obovate), and acute at the top (not obtuse); and different seeds (2 × 2 not 2.5 × 
<quantity id="4CB8FDA2FFE6AC21C3C7F90102419252" box="[234,322,1331,1358]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="7" pageNumber="182" unit="mm" value="1.5">1.5 mm</quantity>
; orbicular not broadly elliptical). The 
<typeStatus id="54FBEEE5FFE6AC21C1FAF90600069252" box="[727,773,1332,1358]" pageId="7" pageNumber="182">type</typeStatus>
specimen was determined as 
<taxonomicName id="4C402BC4FFE6AC21C2FCF96600009271" authority="Boiss." authorityName="Boiss." box="[465,771,1363,1390]" class="Aves" family="Scolopacidae" genus="Arenaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Charadriiformes" pageId="7" pageNumber="182" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="szowitsii">
<emphasis id="B9348C55FFE6AC21C2FCF966012C9272" box="[465,559,1364,1390]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="182">Arenaria</emphasis>
cf. 
<emphasis id="B9348C55FFE6AC21C170F96601B49271" box="[605,695,1364,1389]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="182">szowitsii</emphasis>
Boiss.
</taxonomicName>
, but with having four sepals, four petals and bivalve compressed lenticular capsule, it definitely belongs to 
<taxonomicName id="4C402BC4FFE6AC21C187F9A101FC92B1" box="[682,767,1427,1453]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Caryophyllaceae" genus="Bufonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="7" pageNumber="182" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9348C55FFE6AC21C187F9A101FC92B1" box="[682,767,1427,1453]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="182">Bufonia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
